article.headline: Georgia Southern 79, Savannah State 53
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. (AP) -- Louis Graham scored 20 points and had 11 rebounds, and Willie Dunn added 18 points and 10 rebounds in season-best performances Wednesday night as Georgia Southern routed winless Savannah State 79-53. The Eagles (10-7) -- coming off a record 3-point shooting performance -- had just six-of-19 against the Tigers. But they had no trouble amassing a 51-29 halftime lead and holding on for their fourth straight win. Savannah State (0-23) got within 15-11 at the 13:45 mark of the first half but came no closer. Starting in place of Jean Francois, who sat out the game with a sore foot, freshman forward Graham had his second double-double of the season and also blocked four shots. Dunn was 5-of-10 from the field and hit all eight free throws. Mike Bennett and Donald Carson each scored 15 points for Savannah State, and Sherrard Reddick had 14 rebounds and 12 points for the Tigers. Georgia Southern hit a Southern Conference record 22 three-pointers in Monday's 107-84 victory over Chattanooga.
